Adult.description: Crissal Thrashers are grayer overall with an obvious black mustache stripe that California Thrashers don't have. They also have a yellow eye while California Thrashers have a dark eye.

Adult/immature.description: Curve-billed Thrashers have spotting on the belly not seen on California Thrashers. They also have a yellow eye while California Thrashers have a dark eye.

Adult.description: LeConte's Thrashers are pale sandy gray unlike the brown coloration of the California Thrasher.
